revision.text:
{{notability|date=November 2012}} {{Infobox journal | title = Almagest | discipline = [[History of science]] | editor = Efthymios Nicolaidis, Constantine Skordoulis | publisher = Brepols Publishers | country = | history = 2010-present | frequency = Biannual | abbreviation=Almagest | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.hpdst.gr/publications/almagest | ISSN = 1792-2593 | OCLC = 659522419 }} '''''Almagest''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes contributions evaluating scientific developments. ''Almagest'' addresses the [[philosophy|philosophical]] assumptions behind scientific ideas and developments and the reciprocal influence between historical context and these phenomena. The journal is abstracted in the [[Philosophy Research Index]], STEP - Science and Technology in the European Periphery<ref>{{cite web |url=http://147.156.155.104/?q=node/116 |title=Journals |format= |work=STEP - Science and Technology in the European Periphery |accessdate=2012-11-27 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20121203072120/http://147.156.155.104/?q=node/116 |archive-date=2012-12-03 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> and LibTOC.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.libtoc.com/journal/5105/articles.html |title=Almagest |publisher=LM Information Delivery |work=LibTOC |accessdate=2012-11-27}}</ref>
