'''Hubert Beckers''' (4 November 1806 – 10 March 1889) was a German philosopher known chiefly as an expositor of the philosophy of [[Friedrich Wilhelm Joseph Schelling|Schelling]].
==Biography== He was born at [[Munich]], and studied at the university there. In 1832 he was appointed professor of philosophy at the Lyceum at [[Dillingen an der Donau|Dillingen]], and in 1847 professor of philosophy at the [[University of Munich]]. In 1853 he became a member of the [[Bavarian Academy of Sciences and Humanities|Bavarian Academy of Sciences]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=mxEjAQAAIAAJ&pg=PA539&lpg=PA539&dq=%22Beckers,+Hubert%22+1806+Munich&source=bl&ots=037g8syeVu&sig=yeAaKgFFkBVPoqqrtwoTufiWkHE&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjGyNyQ6t7RAhXI8YMKHWNEAewQ6AEIRzAI#v=onepage&q=%22Beckers%2C%20Hubert%22%201806%20Munich&f=false Meyers Grosses Konversations-Lexikon, Volume 2]</ref> [[File:10-10-23-24-Grab-Hubert-Beckers-Alter-Suedl-Friedhof-Muenchen.JPG|right|thumb|<center>Grave of Hubert Beckers at [[Alter Südfriedhof]] in Munich]] ==Works== * ''Ueber das Wesen des Gefühles'' (1830) &ndash; On the essence of feeling.<ref>[https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Search/Home?lookfor=%22Beckers,HubertKarlPhilipp,1806-1889.%22&type=author&inst= HathiTrust Digital Library] (published works)</ref> * ''Cantica Spiritualia'' (Munich 1845–47). * ''Denkrede auf Schelling'' (Munich 1855) &ndash; Commemorative address of Schelling. * ''Ueber die Bedeutung der Schellingschen Metaphysik'' (Munich 1861) &ndash; On the significance of Schelling's metaphysics. * ''Ueber die Wahre und Bleibende Bedeutung der Naturphilosophie Schelling's'' (1864) &ndash; On the true and lasting significance of Schelling's natural philosophy. * ''Aphorismen über Tod und Unsterblichkeit'' (Munich 1889) &ndash; Aphorisms about death and immortality.
