'''''The Silent World of Doctor and Patient''''' is an influential book{{says who?|date=October 2015}} on [[medical ethics]] written by [[Jay Katz]] and published by [[Free Press (publisher)|The Free Press]] in 1984.<ref>{{Cite journal | title = Book Reviews | journal = Birth | volume = 12 | issue = 1| pages = 47–55 | year = 1985 | doi = 10.1111/j.1523-536X.1985.tb00937.x}}</ref><ref>Hevesi, Dennis. [https://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/20/nyregion/20katz.html "Dr. Jay Katz, 86, Dies; Explorer of Ethics Issues"], ''[[The New York Times]]'', November 19, 2008. Accessed December 11, 2010.</ref>

